The paper proposes a computational model of emotions using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is also relevant to robotics (cs.RO) as it aims to build robots that can have empathy for humans. The use of deep neural networks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulation results, which suggests that it may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
